{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T04:47:10.790Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"L1 and L2 regularization"},{"type":"text","text":" are two core techniques that prevent "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"overfitting"},{"type":"text","text":" in ML models by adding a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"penalty term to the loss function"},{"type":"text","text":" that discourages large weights, thereby reducing model complexity and encouraging the model to focus on the overall structure of data rather than fitting noise."}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Simple definition:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"L1 and L2 regularization are methods used to mitigate overfitting in machine learning models. These techniques are often applied when a model's data set has a large number of features, and a less complex model is needed.\""}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What overfitting is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Overfitting"},{"type":"text","text":" happens when a model learns the training data "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"too well"},{"type":"text","text":", including its noise and outliers, which hampers performance on new, unseen data:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model has "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"low training error"},{"type":"text","text":" but "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"high test error"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model is too "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"complex"},{"type":"text","text":" relative to the data"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model memorizes rather than learns patterns"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Regularization"},{"type":"text","text":" helps prevent this by "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"simplifying the model in a controlled way"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How regularization works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Regularization adds a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"penalty"},{"type":"text","text":" to the cost function the model is trying to minimize:"}]},{"type":"blockMath","attrs":{"latex":"\\text{New Loss} = \\text{Original Loss} + \\lambda \\times \\text{Penalty Term}"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Original Loss"},{"type":"text","text":": SSE (sum of squared errors), cross-entropy, etc.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Penalty Term"},{"type":"text","text":": L1 or L2 norm of weights\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"λ (lambda)"},{"type":"text","text":": Regularization rate (hyperparameter) controlling penalty strength"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Effect"},{"type":"text","text":": By penalizing large weights, regularization forces the model to pay more attention to the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"overall structure"},{"type":"text","text":" rather than fitting training data as closely as possible."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"L1 Regularization (Lasso)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","mark